	<paragraph>
		<paragraph>Notation: a / b</paragraph>
		<paragraph>Applicability: a and b are metrics, not necessarily with the same unit.</paragraph>
		<paragraph>Semantics: division</paragraph>
		<paragraph>Resulting unit: Ratio</paragraph>
		<paragraph>Note that the presence of both linear combinations and ratios make it possible to define any metric of the form</paragraph>
		<paragraph>E k<sub_script>i</sub_script>.m<sub_script>i</sub_script>  / E l<sub_script>i</sub_script>.n<sub_script>i</sub_script></paragraph>
		<span/>
		<paragraph>in terms of elementary metrics m<sub_script>i</sub_script>, n<sub_script>i</sub_script>.</paragraph>
		<paragraph>The metric tool provides a command for defining ratio metrics.</paragraph>
